**Even with a 13% bigger budget, we still managed to spend 92% of our money in
2024 paying contributors for their time.**

So far so good. You can see we've been hard at work spending our esteemed
donors' money on advancing the [mission statement](https://ziglang.org/zsf/#mission-statement).

However, if we look at the trend of donations over time for the year 2024, we
see overall a slow decline. This is why we're doing another fundraiser this year.

## Major Initiatives in 2024

* [Zig 0.13.0 Released](https://ziglang.org/download/0.13.0/release-notes.html)
* [Zig 0.14.0 Released](https://ziglang.org/download/0.14.0/release-notes.html)
  - [Greatly expanded support for more targets](https://ziglang.org/download/0.14.0/release-notes.html#Target-Support) that can be correctly cross-compiled and run on.
  - [Major language enhancements](https://ziglang.org/download/0.14.0/release-notes.html#Language-Changes)
  - [Major standard library enhancements](https://ziglang.org/download/0.14.0/release-notes.html#Standard-Library)
  - [Major build system enhancements](https://ziglang.org/download/0.14.0/release-notes.html#Build-System)
  - Zig 0.14.1 released with bug fixes only.

